items.title: Sanders and Hawley’s Interest Rate Cap Would Ban Their Union Allies’ Credit Cards
items.description: They want to cap interest rates at 10 percent, but most major unions’ member benefits include credit cards that charge well in excess of that.

items.title: In Defense of Ben Sasse
items.description: Tentative audit findings fail to back up the barrage of media attacks the former university president and senator has faced over expenses.

items.description: Plus: Donald Trump considers a real-estate opportunity in Gaza.

items.title: Attention Must Be Paid: The Tax Cuts and Jobs Act Is Set to Expire
items.description: Expiring provisions promise tax hikes if not extended.

items.title: Two Cheers for Tariffs
items.description: Not every tariff is a boon, nor is every one a bane. But they can provide long-term gains well in excess of their short-term costs.
